{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Made By / Mohammed Magdy Hagras (Moresa)**              \n","# **Reg / 221010763**"],"metadata":{"id":"Mg-IxXWRIhlC"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Dataset Links:\n","\n","SSCD1 (UCI SMS Spam): [Link 1](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1db2T8XtTPW94CAhYfuB7EroF5Kx9wsHm/view?usp=drive_link)\n","\n","SSCD2 (Dataset 2): [Link 2](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1rINGyHTtnuf2AVpa8iychdw3keIHK8bU/view?usp=drive_link)"],"metadata":{"id":"TZBsPylXIjxy"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# General Imports"],"metadata":{"id":"nMOWHDg_teAC"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","import re\n","import nltk\n","from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer\n","nltk.download('punkt_tab', quiet=True)\n","from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n","from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer, TfidfTransformer\n","from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n","from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n","from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n","import warnings\n","from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')\n","\n","# Disable warnings to ensure a clean output in the notebook\n","warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n","\n","# Download the required NLTK resources for text processing\n","nltk.download('punkt', quiet=True)\n","nltk.download('wordnet', quiet=True)\n","nltk.download('omw-1.4', quiet=True)\n","\n","# Initialize the lemmatizer for text normalization\n","lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()\n","\n","# Define the text cleaning function\n","def clean_text(text):\n","    if not isinstance(text, str):\n","        return \"\"\n","    # Convert to lowercase\n","    text = text.lower()\n","    # Remove non-alphabetic characters\n","    text = re.sub(r'[^a-z\\s]', ' ', text)\n","    # Tokenize the string into individual words\n","    tokens = nltk.word_tokenize(text)\n","    # Lemmatize each word to its root form (e.g., 'running' -> 'run')\n","    tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(token) for token in tokens if token.isalpha()]\n","    # Rejoin tokens into a single cleaned string\n","    return ' '.join(tokens)"],"metadata":{"id":"2f4ZpLkdtijZ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775863131487,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":2512,"user":{"displayName":"Mohamed","userId":"02965195113184872926"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"outputId":"9d605e7d-600b-4d0a-ca92-816ec47f86c3"},"execution_count":12,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Drive already mounted at /content/drive; to attempt to forcibly remount, call drive.mount(\"/content/drive\", force_remount=True).\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# 1.0 SMS Spam Detection - SSCD1 (Dataset 1) ****\n","\n","# 1.1 Pre-Processing\n","We start by loading the first dataset and applying text normalization. We will use Lemmatization to return words to their base form and TF-IDF to weigh the importance of each word in the messages."],"metadata":{"id":"rHj3DHe0uRSn"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["print(\"Loading SSCD1...\")\n","\n","# Specify the file path for SSCD1\n","file_path1 = \"/content/drive/MyDrive/path_to_data/SSCD1 (sms_spam_no_header.csv).csv\"\n","\n","# Manually handle formatting issues by reading line by line\n","with open(file_path1, 'r', encoding='utf-8', errors='ignore') as f:\n","    lines = f.readlines()\n","\n","data1 = []\n","for line in lines:\n","    line = line.strip()\n","    if not line: continue\n","    # Strip leading quotes\n","    if line.startswith('\"'): line = line[1:]\n","    # Split by the specific label/message separator\n","    if '\",\"' in line:\n","        label, message = line.split('\",\"', 1)\n","        data1.append([label.strip('\"'), message.strip('\"')])\n","\n","# Create DataFrame and apply cleaning\n","df1 = pd.DataFrame(data1, columns=['label', 'message'])\n","df1['label'] = df1['label'].str.lower().str.strip()\n","df1['clean_message'] = df1['message'].apply(clean_text)\n","\n","print(\"SSCD1 Shape:\", df1.shape)\n","print(df1['label'].value_counts())\n","\n","# Split the dataset before vectorization to prevent Data Leakage\n","y1 = df1['label']\n","X_train_text1, X_test_text1, y_train1, y_test1 = train_test_split(\n","    df1['clean_message'], y1, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y1\n",")\n","\n","# Convert text into numerical counts (Bag of Words)\n","# Fit only on training data\n","bow1 = CountVectorizer().fit(X_train_text1)\n","\n","# Apply TF-IDF transformation\n","tfidf1 = TfidfTransformer()\n","X_train1 = tfidf1.fit_transform(bow1.transform(X_train_text1))\n","X_test1 = tfidf1.transform(bow1.transform(X_test_text1))"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"hZgPwpzXui1W","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775863138392,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":6890,"user":{"displayName":"Mohamed","userId":"02965195113184872926"}},"outputId":"c42a7712-16ba-4eff-ba28-0928e89f5473"},"execution_count":13,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loading SSCD1...\n","SSCD1 Shape: (5574, 3)\n","label\n","ham     4827\n","spam     747\n","Name: count, dtype: int64\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# 1.2 Training and Evaluating Multinomial Naive Bayes (NB)\n","We train the first model on SSCD1. Naive Bayes is probabilistic and works well with text frequency."],"metadata":{"id":"wJGOdy1duoEu"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Initialize and train the Naive Bayes model for SSCD1\n","nb1 = MultinomialNB().fit(X_train1, y_train1)\n","\n","# Calculate and print accuracy for Naive Bayes\n","nb1_acc = accuracy_score(y_test1, nb1.predict(X_test1))\n","print(f\"SSCD1 - NB Accuracy : {nb1_acc*100:.2f}%\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"3hkyE9Ncut_l","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775863138440,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":34,"user":{"displayName":"Mohamed","userId":"02965195113184872926"}},"outputId":"5d16e0a5-cc82-44b5-e6ff-27cfd298471d"},"execution_count":14,